The paper deals with the issue of insider attacks in database systems, which falls under the domain of database security (cs.DB) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The proposed solution involves using a blockchain network to store metadata about tuples from an SQL database, which involves aspects of distributed systems (cs.DC) and cryptography (cs.CY). Finally, the implementation of the technique involves using Hyperledger Fabric and Composer REST API, which are tools commonly used in software engineering (cs.SE).
